Durban - A jewellery store has been robbed at Phoenix Plaza a short while ago. According to Prem Balram from Reaction Unit SA five men armed with AK47s opened fire inside the jewellery store. He said when officers arrived at approximately 09:38am SAPS was already in attendance. "Jewellery and an undisclosed amount of cash was taken. Suspects fled in a black Mercedes Benz which was later recovered in Bambhayi informal settlement by law enforcement," said Balram. He said suspects were still on the run. KZN police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala confirmed the shooting incident. She said police were still at the scene which was active. "Details are still sketchy at the moment." Last month the Daily News reported that a man was arrested in connection with the robbery of a cellular phone store at the Phoenix Plaza. Brigadier Jay Naicker, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said that employees of a cellphone service provider were performing their duties when they were accosted by two unknown men who threatened them with a firearm. The men removed 30 cellphones and placed them into a bag. POST